FIRE
  Fire deck guns, artillery, or a fortress's guns at a ship or sector.

SYNTAX
  fire ship <uid-spec> ship <target-uid>
  fire ship <uid-spec> sect <x,y>
  fire land <uid-spec> ship <target-uid>
  fire land <uid-spec> sect <x,y>
  fire fort <x,y>       ship <target-uid>
  fire fort <x,y>       sect <x,y>

DESCRIPTION
  Three kinds of unit can fire guns:
    ship  - a ship with deck guns and shells aboard (effic >= 60%)
    land  - an artillery-capable land unit (effic >= 40%), not loaded
            on a ship or another unit
    fort  - a fortress sector (effic >= 5%) with >= 5 militia aboard

  <uid-spec> works like 'ship'/'land': a uid ("5"), a range ("0-5"),
  or "*" for all of yours matching. <x,y> is your capital-relative
  sector coordinate.

  Unlike bombing or torpedoes, gunfire has NO miss chance: once a
  firer is in range and eligible, damage lands every time. Damage
  scales with the firer's efficiency and the number of guns it can
  bring to bear, with some randomness in the dice roll per gun.

  Ammo: firing consumes shells. Ships need roughly half a shell per
  gun fired and will fire fewer guns if short on shells. A fortress
  burns exactly 1 shell per shot regardless of gun count. An
  artillery unit's ammo requirement is fixed by its type; firing
  with less than that on hand still fires, but at reduced (scaled
  down) effectiveness.

  Ships also spend 15 mobility points firing their guns.

  Counter-fire: if you fire on an enemy ship and it survives with
  its own guns and ammo still usable, it fires back at you once,
  immediately, in the same command. (Sectors and land units hit by
  gunfire do not currently fire back.)

  Friendly fire (hitting your own ship or sector) does not generate
  a news item.

KNOWN GAPS (v1)
  - No auto-resupply of shells from a nearby sector/warehouse before
    firing; a unit with 0 shells on hand simply can't fire.
  - Return fire is a single reprisal shot, not 4.4.1's full
    multi-defender pooled return fire from everyone in range.
  - Damaged ships/units do not automatically retreat.

EXAMPLE
  fire ship 3 ship 12          ship 3 fires on ship 12
  fire ship 0-2 sect 4,-1      ships 0-2 each shell sector 4,-1
  fire land 5 sect 1,0         artillery unit 5 shells sector 1,0
  fire fort 0,0 ship 7         your capital's fortress fires on ship 7

